WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Around the world in 80 days, by Jules Verne, chapter 1.

00:17.000 --> 00:21.000
It is London in 1872.

00:21.000 --> 00:28.000
And this is Mr. Phileus Fogg's house.

00:40.000 --> 00:45.000
Mr. Phileus Fogg is an English gentleman.

00:45.000 --> 00:50.000
He lives in London.

00:50.000 --> 00:55.000
He hasn't got a wife or children.

00:55.000 --> 01:02.000
But he has got a French servant, Paspartou.

01:04.000 --> 01:09.000
Phogg goes to his club every day.

01:10.000 --> 01:15.000
He eats at his club at 12 o'clock.

01:15.000 --> 01:19.000
In the afternoon he reads there.

01:20.000 --> 01:28.000
In the evening he eats there again.

01:28.000 --> 01:32.000
Then he talks with his friends.

01:32.000 --> 01:38.000
And at midnight he goes home.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
Paspartou is happy.

01:42.000 --> 01:48.000
He wants a quiet job.

01:48.000 --> 01:57.000
But one evening Phogg sees something interesting in the times.

01:57.000 --> 02:07.000
Gentlemen thief takes 5,000 pounds from the Bank of England.

02:07.000 --> 02:13.000
At the club Phogg's friends talk.

02:13.000 --> 02:18.000
That gentleman thief can't go far.

02:18.000 --> 02:21.000
Says Ralph.

02:21.000 --> 02:29.000
With trains and ships, today's detectives move fast.

02:29.000 --> 02:37.000
But thieves can move fast too, Flanagan says.

02:37.000 --> 02:44.000
Today you can go round the world in 80 days.

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
Says Phogg.

02:47.000 --> 02:54.000
Do it and I pay you 20,000 pounds.

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
Says Stewart.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.000
I'm leaving tonight.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
Then answers Phogg.

03:04.000 --> 03:09.000
Perhaps I can't do it, Stewart.

03:09.000 --> 03:18.000
But then I pay you 20,000 pounds.

03:18.000 --> 03:25.000
The train for France leaves before 9 in the evening.

03:25.000 --> 03:36.000
Phogg must be back in London by the 21st of December.

03:36.000 --> 03:43.000
Phogg gives 20,000 pounds in a bag to his servant.

03:43.000 --> 03:48.000
We're leaving for France, he says.

03:48.000 --> 03:54.000
Paspartou isn't very happy.

03:54.000 --> 04:02.000
They go to France.

04:02.000 --> 04:17.000
Then they take a train to Italy and a ship to Portside in Egypt.

04:17.000 --> 04:27.000
When their ship arrives in Suez, an English detective, Mr. Fix, is waiting.

04:27.000 --> 04:32.000
He's looking for the gentleman thief.

04:32.000 --> 04:37.000
Phogg visits the passport office.

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
Mr. Fix sees him there.

04:42.000 --> 04:47.000
It's the gentleman thief, he thinks.

04:47.000 --> 04:50.000
I must tell London.

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
Chapter Two.

05:06.000 --> 05:11.000
Fix looks at Paspartou.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.000
Where are you going?

05:15.000 --> 05:17.000
He asks.

05:17.000 --> 05:23.000
Around the world says Paspartou.

05:23.000 --> 05:30.000
But right now I need some new shirts.

05:30.000 --> 05:37.000
Fix takes him to a shop and leaves him there.

05:37.000 --> 05:43.000
Then he sends a telegram to London.

05:43.000 --> 05:48.000
The gentleman thief is going to Bombay.

05:48.000 --> 05:54.000
Stop. Fix.

05:54.000 --> 06:06.000
Later he gets on the ship for Bombay with Phogg and Paspartou.

06:07.000 --> 06:15.000
It is the 20th of October.

06:15.000 --> 06:23.000
They all arrive in Bombay, two days early.

06:23.000 --> 06:32.000
At 4.30 in the afternoon, Phogg and Paspartou leave the ship.

06:33.000 --> 06:40.000
They want to get a train across India to Calcutta.

06:40.000 --> 06:46.000
It leaves at 8 o'clock.

06:46.000 --> 06:51.000
First Phogg goes to the passport office.

06:51.000 --> 06:56.000
Then he eats at the station.

06:56.000 --> 07:02.000
Paspartou visits the temple at Malibar Hill.

07:02.000 --> 07:07.000
But he doesn't take off his shoes.

07:07.000 --> 07:11.000
The priests get angry.

07:11.000 --> 07:19.000
They take his shoes and Paspartou runs away.

07:19.000 --> 07:32.000
Phogg and Paspartou get on the train.

07:32.000 --> 07:36.000
But Fix stays in Bombay.

07:36.000 --> 07:43.000
He is waiting for a telegram from London.

07:43.000 --> 07:53.000
After three days, the train stops.

07:53.000 --> 08:03.000
The railway from Colby to Alalabad isn't ready.

08:03.000 --> 08:06.000
Some men are building the railway.

08:06.000 --> 08:15.000
But there are 80 kilometres without a railway between Colby and Alalabad.

08:15.000 --> 08:22.000
In Colby, Paspartou gets some new shoes.

08:22.000 --> 08:33.000
He also finds an elephant to take them to Alalabad.

08:33.000 --> 08:40.000
They stop near a temple in the village of Pelaji.

08:40.000 --> 08:44.000
The old Indian prince is dead.

08:44.000 --> 08:55.000
His young wife, the princess, must die with him in a big fire.

08:55.000 --> 09:02.000
We must help that woman, says Phogg.

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
The priests start the fire.

09:05.000 --> 09:11.000
Through the smoke, Phogg sees something beautiful.

09:11.000 --> 09:20.000
The prince stands up and takes the princess out of the fire.

09:20.000 --> 09:25.000
The prince and the princess come nearer.

09:25.000 --> 09:30.000
Phogg sees that the man is not the prince.

09:30.000 --> 09:35.000
It is Paspartou in the prince's clothes.

09:35.000 --> 09:41.000
Quickly, let's go, says Paspartou to Phogg quietly.

09:41.000 --> 09:48.000
Suddenly, the priests see the prince's body on the fire.

09:48.000 --> 09:58.000
They see that the man in the prince's clothes is not the prince and they become angry.

09:58.000 --> 10:08.000
Phogg, Paspartou and the princess leave very quickly on the elephant.

10:19.000 --> 10:24.000
Chapter 3

10:24.000 --> 10:30.000
At last, they arrive in Alalabad.

10:30.000 --> 10:36.000
Phogg buys some European clothes for the princess.

10:36.000 --> 10:42.000
What a beautiful woman, he thinks.

10:43.000 --> 10:51.000
On the train going to Calcutta, she speaks for the first time.

10:51.000 --> 10:55.000
My name's Mrs. Aouda.

10:55.000 --> 10:58.000
Thank you for helping me.

10:58.000 --> 11:02.000
But I don't know what to do now.

11:02.000 --> 11:07.000
I can never go home.

11:07.000 --> 11:12.000
We can take you to Hong Kong, Phogg says.

11:12.000 --> 11:16.000
Thank you, says Mrs. Aouda.

11:16.000 --> 11:21.000
I have a cousin there.

11:21.000 --> 11:27.000
At Calcutta station, a policeman stops them.

11:27.000 --> 11:31.000
He takes them to see a judge.

11:31.000 --> 11:36.000
Mrs. Aouda goes to.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
Fix is in Calcutta.

11:40.000 --> 11:46.000
Detectives must move fast to find gentleman thieves.

11:46.000 --> 11:49.000
He's waiting in court.

11:49.000 --> 11:54.000
But Phogg and his friends don't see him.

11:54.000 --> 11:57.000
Why are we here?

11:57.000 --> 12:05.000
For breaking the rules in a temple, says the judge.

12:05.000 --> 12:08.000
In pillage, asks Phogg.

12:08.000 --> 12:14.000
No, in Bombay, says the judge.

12:14.000 --> 12:21.000
And he puts Paspatu's shoes on the table.

12:21.000 --> 12:28.000
You must go to prison for this, says the judge.

12:28.000 --> 12:38.000
But Phogg gives £2,000 to the court, and they're free again.

12:38.000 --> 12:42.000
They get onto the ship for Hong Kong.

12:42.000 --> 12:46.000
Fix follows them.

12:46.000 --> 12:49.000
But Paspatu sees him.

12:49.000 --> 12:56.000
Perhaps he's a detective, he thinks.

12:56.000 --> 13:05.000
Perhaps he's working for Mr. Stewart from the gentleman's club in London.

13:05.000 --> 13:14.000
In Hong Kong, Mrs. Aouda learns that her cousin now lives in Holland.

13:14.000 --> 13:21.000
Come with us to Europe, says.

13:21.000 --> 13:27.000
Paspatu wants to buy three tickets on the Carnatic.

13:27.000 --> 13:34.000
It leaves for Yokohama in Japan the next morning.

13:34.000 --> 13:44.000
But at the ticket office, he learns that it's leaving early that evening.

13:44.000 --> 13:49.000
Paspatu meets Fix near the ticket office.

13:49.000 --> 13:55.000
Come for a drink, says Fix.

13:55.000 --> 13:59.000
Fix tells Paspatu,

13:59.000 --> 14:09.000
I think your Mr. Phogg is a gentleman thief, and I want to arrest him.

14:09.000 --> 14:26.000
Paspatu doesn't want to help Fix, but the detective buys drink after drink.

14:26.000 --> 14:33.000
Paspatu goes to sleep on the table.

14:33.000 --> 14:38.000
Now he can't tell Phogg about the Carnatic.

14:38.000 --> 15:00.000
Things fix. It leaves tonight, but without Phogg.

15:00.000 --> 15:03.000
Chapter 4

15:03.000 --> 15:07.000
Later, Paspatu wakes up.

15:07.000 --> 15:13.000
He goes onto the Carnatic, and the ship leaves.

15:13.000 --> 15:20.000
But Phogg and Mrs. Aouda aren't with him.

15:20.000 --> 15:30.000
Next morning, Phogg and Mrs. Aouda go to get on the Carnatic, but it isn't there.

15:30.000 --> 15:33.000
Fix arrives.

15:33.000 --> 15:38.000
The Carnatics on its way to Japan, he says.

15:38.000 --> 15:44.000
And the next ship to Yokohama leaves next week.

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
Where's Paspatu?

15:46.000 --> 15:49.000
asks Mrs. Aouda.

15:49.000 --> 15:55.000
I don't know, says Phogg, but we must go on without him.

15:55.000 --> 15:59.000
We must find another ship.

15:59.000 --> 16:05.000
Phogg finds a small ship, the Tanka Deer, to go to Shanghai.

16:05.000 --> 16:11.000
There, they can get a big ship to Yokohama.

16:11.000 --> 16:13.000
Can I go with you?

16:13.000 --> 16:15.000
asks Fix.

16:15.000 --> 16:20.000
Of course, Phogg answers.

16:30.000 --> 16:37.000
The Tanka Deer travels through storms.

16:37.000 --> 16:42.000
And at last, arrives near Shanghai.

16:42.000 --> 16:47.000
Suddenly, they see a big ship in front of them.

16:47.000 --> 16:51.000
It's on its way to Yokohama.

16:51.000 --> 16:58.000
Signal to that ship, says Phogg.

16:58.000 --> 17:15.000
Pass Paspatu arrives in Yokohama, but he has no money.

17:15.000 --> 17:22.000
He leaves the Carnatic and finds work in Mr. Batulka's Circus.

17:29.000 --> 17:36.000
I can go to America with the Circus, he thinks.

17:36.000 --> 17:42.000
Phogg, Mrs. Aouda and Fix, get on the big ship.

17:42.000 --> 17:52.000
And a week later, they arrive in Japan.

17:52.000 --> 17:56.000
The Carnatic is in Yokohama.

17:57.000 --> 18:02.000
Phogg and Mrs. Aouda go on to the Carnatic.

18:02.000 --> 18:07.000
They find Pass Paspatu's name in the book of passengers' names,

18:07.000 --> 18:11.000
but they can't find Pass Paspatu.

18:11.000 --> 18:16.000
Their ship leaves for San Francisco in a few hours.

18:16.000 --> 18:22.000
Before they leave, Phogg goes to the Circus.

18:22.000 --> 18:25.000
Pass Paspatu sees him there.

18:25.000 --> 18:27.000
Mr. Phogg!

18:27.000 --> 18:33.000
He says happily.

18:33.000 --> 18:37.000
Phogg wants to take Pass Paspatu with him.

18:37.000 --> 18:48.000
But first, he must pay Mr. Batulka.

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
At six o'clock in the evening,

18:51.000 --> 18:59.000
Phogg, Pass Paspatu and Mrs. Aouda go on to the American ship.

18:59.000 --> 19:02.000
Fix follows them.

19:02.000 --> 19:17.000
Chapter 5

19:17.000 --> 19:22.000
I'm sorry about Hong Kong, says Pass Paspatu.

19:22.000 --> 19:27.000
I don't usually drink much, but...

19:28.000 --> 19:34.000
Later, Pass Paspatu sees Fix on the ship.

19:34.000 --> 19:40.000
My master isn't a gentleman thief, he says.

19:40.000 --> 19:44.000
Listen, says Fix.

19:44.000 --> 19:50.000
I now have papers from London to arrest Mr. Phogg.

19:50.000 --> 19:53.000
But I can't stop him now.

19:53.000 --> 19:56.000
It must be in England.

19:56.000 --> 19:59.000
When we get there...

20:06.000 --> 20:11.000
They arrive in San Francisco in the morning.

20:11.000 --> 20:17.000
The New York train leaves that evening.

20:17.000 --> 20:22.000
Phogg and Mrs. Aouda meet Fix in the street.

20:22.000 --> 20:26.000
I am travelling to Europe now.

20:26.000 --> 20:29.000
Can we travel together?

20:29.000 --> 20:31.000
He asks.

20:31.000 --> 20:37.000
Of course, answers Phogg.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.000
They walk into a meeting.

20:40.000 --> 20:43.000
Camera feel for Judge!

20:43.000 --> 20:46.000
Shout the people on the left.

20:46.000 --> 20:49.000
Mandy boy for Judge!

20:49.000 --> 20:52.000
Shout the people on the right.

20:52.000 --> 20:57.000
Then they start fighting.

20:57.000 --> 21:08.000
One man wants to fight Phogg, but Fix stands in front of him and stops him.

21:08.000 --> 21:13.000
Pass Paspatu finds it all very strange.

21:14.000 --> 21:20.000
So, Mr. Fix is helping us now, he thinks?

21:20.000 --> 21:29.000
Phogg, Mrs. Aouda, Pass Paspatu and Fix get on the train that evening.

21:29.000 --> 21:37.000
They cross one old bridge very fast and it falls into the river behind them.

21:44.000 --> 21:48.000
Then, some Sioux Indians arrive.

21:48.000 --> 21:51.000
They kill some passengers.

21:51.000 --> 21:54.000
Pass Paspatu fights them.

21:54.000 --> 22:00.000
But they take him and ride away with him.

22:04.000 --> 22:10.000
Phogg, Mrs. Aouda and Fix get off the train.

22:11.000 --> 22:15.000
Phogg goes to look for Pass Paspatu.

22:15.000 --> 22:19.000
He finds him and brings him back.

22:19.000 --> 22:29.000
But they must wait until evening, until the next train to New York.

22:29.000 --> 22:34.000
How can we travel fast over the snow?

22:34.000 --> 22:36.000
Things fix.

22:36.000 --> 22:41.000
On a slange with sails.

22:41.000 --> 22:45.000
Soon, they arrive in Omaha.

22:45.000 --> 22:51.000
There, they take a train to New York.

22:51.000 --> 22:56.000
They arrive in New York 45 minutes late.

22:56.000 --> 23:02.000
Their ship, the China, is on its way to Liverpool.

23:05.000 --> 23:28.000
Chapter 6

23:29.000 --> 23:43.000
The next morning, Phogg, Mrs. Aouda, Pass Paspatu and Fix leave on a small ship, the Henrietta, going to France.

23:43.000 --> 23:53.000
Later, Phogg gives the sailors money and they agree to go to Liverpool, not to France.

23:53.000 --> 23:59.000
The sailors lock the captain in his room.

23:59.000 --> 24:06.000
The Henrietta is in the middle of the Atlantic and there's no coal.

24:06.000 --> 24:14.000
Burn all the wood on the ship, says Phogg.

24:14.000 --> 24:26.000
The ship arrives in Queenstown, in the south of Ireland, and there's no more wood on it.

24:26.000 --> 24:34.000
Let's get off here, says Phogg to Mrs. Aouda, Pass Paspatu and Fix.

24:34.000 --> 24:38.000
Fix doesn't arrest Phogg in Queenstown.

24:38.000 --> 24:44.000
He's waiting for them to arrive in England.

24:44.000 --> 24:48.000
They get on a train and travel to Dublin.

24:48.000 --> 24:54.000
There, they get a fast ship to Liverpool.

24:54.000 --> 25:04.000
In Liverpool, Fix arrests Phogg at last and takes him to prison.

25:04.000 --> 25:09.000
In prison, Phogg looks at his diary.

25:09.000 --> 25:14.000
At two o'clock he looks at his watch.

25:14.000 --> 25:24.000
There's time to go to London on a fast train and to be at my club by 845 this evening.

25:24.000 --> 25:27.000
He thinks.

25:27.000 --> 25:35.000
At half past three, Fix arrives with Mrs. Aouda and Pass Paspatu.

25:35.000 --> 25:40.000
I'm sorry, Mr. Phogg, says Fix.

25:40.000 --> 25:45.000
The gentleman thief, James Strand, is in prison.

25:45.000 --> 25:49.000
You're free to go.

25:49.000 --> 25:56.000
Angrily, Phogg punches Fix in the face.

25:56.000 --> 26:03.000
Then Phogg, Mrs. Aouda and Pass Paspatu run to Liverpool station.

26:03.000 --> 26:08.000
They get a fast train to London.

26:08.000 --> 26:12.000
The train arrives at ten minutes to nine.

26:12.000 --> 26:24.000
Phogg is five minutes late for his meeting with Stuart.

26:24.000 --> 26:35.000
Phogg doesn't want to get to his club late, so he goes home with Mrs. Aouda and Pass Paspatu.

26:35.000 --> 26:44.000
Around the world in eighty days and five minutes, he's the loser.

26:44.000 --> 26:54.000
He has only twenty thousand pounds in the bank and he must give it all to Stuart.

26:54.000 --> 27:00.000
I'm sorry for bringing you here to a poor man's home.

27:00.000 --> 27:04.000
He says to Mrs. Aouda the next morning.

27:04.000 --> 27:06.000
Will you marry me?

27:06.000 --> 27:08.000
asks Mrs. Aouda.

27:08.000 --> 27:13.000
Yes, says Phogg.

27:13.000 --> 27:18.000
That afternoon, Phogg tells Pass Paspatu.

27:18.000 --> 27:26.000
I want to marry Mrs. Aouda tomorrow, the twenty-third of December.

27:26.000 --> 27:31.000
Can you speak to the people at Marleben Church about it?

27:31.000 --> 27:35.000
Soon, Pass Paspatu returns.

27:35.000 --> 27:39.000
Today's the twenty-first of December.

27:39.000 --> 27:46.000
When you travel east around the world, you get an extra day.

27:46.000 --> 27:55.000
You aren't late for your meeting at the club after all, but you must run.

27:55.000 --> 28:00.000
At a quarter to nine, Phogg enters his club.

28:00.000 --> 28:08.000
I win, he says to Stuart, wears by twenty thousand pounds.

28:08.000 --> 28:15.000
Next Monday, Phogg, the world traveler, marries Mrs. Aouda.

28:15.000 --> 28:18.000
He's a very happy man.

